President Obama and his national security team received a briefing from U.S. Ambassador to Afghanistan Ryan Crocker and Commander of NATO's International Security Assistance Force (ISAF) General John Allen. The briefing discussed the situation in Afghanistan, the progress of the coalition campaign, the development of Afghan National Security Forces, and support for the Afghan government's transition to taking the lead in security. The President reiterated his commitment to a political solution in Afghanistan and expressed support for Secretary Clinton's regional engagement agenda, including an international meeting in Bonn in December 2011.